data.title: XTL Biopharmaceuticals Ltd. received Nasdaq delist determination as a "public shell"; plans to request hearing.
data.description: In Ramat Gan, Israel, on February 27, 2026, XTL Biopharmaceuticals Ltd. (Nasdaq: XTLB) (TASE: XTLB.TA) disclosed receiving a letter on February 25, 2026, from The Nasdaq Stock Market LLC's Listing Qualifications Department. The communication stated that the Company is deemed a "public shell" as per Nasdaq Listing Rule 5101, casting doubts on the continued validity of the listing for XTL's American Depositary Shares (ADSs). To challenge this assessment, XTL plans to request a hearing with a Nasdaq Hearings Panel. During this appeal process, the suspension and delisting of the ADSs will be put on hold pending the Panel’s decision.
